{
  "texts": [
    "IoT technology helps in optimizing resource allocation and reducing waste, leading to a 15-20% reduction in overall operational costs.",
    "Mahdavinejad et al. (2018) by integrating with IoT in smart livestock farming, ensuring transparent and secure data exchange among farmers, improving livestock management, and tracking agricultural products throughout the supply chain (Alshehri 2023).",
    "Robotics Robotics in agriculture has emerged as a transformative solution to address labor shortages, enhance productivity, and reduce operational costs in the agricultural sector.",
    "The integration of computer-based sensors, actuators, and robotics systems in farming operations has significantly advanced precision agriculture, greenhouse farming, and field management (Roldán et al. 2018; Siddik et al. 2016).",
    "These technologies enable tasks such as planting, harvesting, environmental monitoring, crop inspection, and treatment to be efficiently automated, leading to increased efficiency and sustainability in agricultural practices (Khadatkar et al. 2022)."
  ]
}